Queries . Since semantic-search queries are derived from the same embedding model as the data, we assume that distributions of vectors from Movies and Reviews tables are similar. This is supported by Figure 5, which shows the distribution of pairwise cosine distances for vector pairs from each table and their mixture.

Indexes. We evaluate two widely implemented ANN indexing methods: HNSW and IVFFlat . For the HNSW index, we explore the following hyperparameter configurations:
- Construction parameters: ( M,ef construction ) ∈ { (5 , 25) , (10 , 50) , (15 , 75) }
- Search parameter: ef search ∈ { 1 , 10 , 40 , 100 , 200 , 500 , 1000 }
For the IVFFlat index, we vary the number of centroids to control the trade-off depending on dataset size:
- Construction parameters: clusters = { small : (100 , 500) , medium : (300 , 1200) , large : (750 , 1600) } . These ranges roughly follow the common C ≈ √ N heuristic, where C is number of clusters, and N is the dataset size.
- Search parameters: n probes = { 1 , 5 , 10 , 20 , 50 , 150 , 300 }
